The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Protest against Hidco
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Protest against Hidco
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Residents of Chhapna held a public convention in Rajarhat on Sunday protesting the manner in which land was taken by Hidco for New Town. Debabrata Banerjee, a former secretary of the land and land reforms department, said Hidco had provided incomplete information regarding land compensation package in a recent newspaper advertisement where his name was mentioned.        
	Accidents: Five persons died in four accidents in Howrah on Sunday. Swapna Porel, 14, and Rabin Mandal, 30, died after being hit by trucks. A minibus ran over Mohan Pal, 70. In the afternoon, a truck rammed into a bike killing two and injuring one.        
	Fire: A parked motorcycle caught fire on the premises of a building on Burdwan Road on Sunday. Four tenders doused the flames.        
	Theft: Nearly 70 watches were stolen from a Ranikuthi shop on Sunday. A resident found the locks broken and alerted the owner.        
	Death: A 42-year-old security guard, Gopalchandra Ghosh, died after being hit by a truck on BT Road on Sunday. Ghosh was taken to Balaram Seva Mandir where he was declared dead on arrival.                                                                                                                                                          
